title: Grateful Dead Live at Sullivan Stadium on 1989-07-02
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.8 MHz) >KORG AudioGate 4 > Adobe Audition CC 2015 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Playin' In The Band-> Crazy Fingers-> Wang Dang Doodle, We Can Run But We Can't Hide, Tennessee Jed, Queen Jane Approximately, To Lay Me Down, Cassidy, Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Friend Of The Devil, Truckin'-> He's Gone-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> Dear Mr. Fantasy-> Hey Jude Reprise-> Sugar Magnolia, E: The Mighty Quinn

reviews.review_text:
Finally! Thank you Charlie!

Can't believe I finally have a quality copy of this show, let alone this crispy matrix transfer that has all the benefits of both the uncirculating soundboard mixed with your audience magix transfer!

Highlights: Playin -> Crazy Fingers opener?!?!
Wang Dang Doodle... super dark
Queen Jane is top notch
To Lay Me Down 

FOTD
Eyes
Dear Mr. Fantasy is the best ever...
Sugar Mags

Basically the entire show is the undersung best of summer 89', which is saying alot. 

Best shows of Summer 89'... Foxboro 7/2, Philly 7/7, Alpine Valley 7/19... Essentially the finest of 89'. Some Fall shows equal... But this is the highest of highs... totally "without a net"... no setlist. Total synchronicity. Thank you CM

Great Memories It was in the high 90's and humid as hell.  In other words a perfect summer day in New England.  The boys were hot!  So hot they had to bring out the hoses during the 2nd set to cool off the heads.  The drum circle was in full force.  But most of all the music was sweet!
Thanks for sharing and bringing it back to me.
Nice MTX! With some slight treble cut on the EQ, this recording is stunning! It's also a hell of a show: amazing cohesion, jamming and a hot, hot Garcia.

Summer Tour of '89 This recording is stunning.
